transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra. Hello? Hello, how are we doing, sir? Okay. I'm pulling your prescription.

Speaker 2: Well, I want to cancel it. Mr. Roy Crumpler in Seville, Florida.

Speaker 1: Yep, that's me. Any health concern or you just don't need refill often?

Speaker 2: Pardon me? Any health concern or you just don't need refill at the moment? You want me to advise the pharmacy to pause your prescription?

Speaker 1: So you're just going to order as needed?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I don't want to be on a normal prescription every month basis.

Speaker 1: Okay. I'm going to tell the pharmacy to pause. What happened, they just fulfilled what the doctor wrote in the prescription initially but you don't have to follow that.

Speaker 2: Every month is not a requirement. You don't have to get pills that you don't need every month.

Speaker 1: So I'm going to advise the pharmacy to pause. They usually pause you up to half a year and then you don't get it every month anymore and then you can lock your pricing by getting a refill once or twice a year, maybe 10 pills if you don't need 25.

Speaker 2: You don't even have to get 25. It's up to you, okay? So let me advise the pharmacy to pause that prescription so you don't get it every month, okay?

Speaker 1: Well, they won't send it until I call them, right?

Speaker 2: Yeah, they'll pause you and then you can call to reorder.

Speaker 1: Okay, give me one moment.
